Hollywood movie studio 20th Century Fox has recently released the first official trailer for ‘The King’s Man’ which is a third installment of the Kingsman series of films. Based on the comic book series of the same name, it has been revealed that the third entry would feature an entirely new cast of characters as it explores the origins of how the secret spy service came to be. The prequel stars Ralph Fiennes, Harris Dickinson, Liam Neeson, Daniel Brühl, Rhys Ifans, Gemma Arterton, Aaron Taylor-Johnson, Charles Dance, and Djimon Hounsou among many others. In addition to featuring an absolutely stellar cast, Kingsman 1 and 2 director Matthew Vaughn has returned to the handle the project. Although the latest installment to the trilogy seems not to feature a lot of laughs like the previous films, Vaughn has still referred to The King’s Man as an action-comedy. The King’s Man is set for release on February 14th, 2020. Watch the first official trailer of ‘The King’s Man’ via YouTube below;  